\section{TMD factorization and non-perturbative evolution}
\label{eq:tmdfactorization}

The purpose of this talk is to summarize 
results recently presented in Ref.~\cite{Collins:2014jpa}.
We will discuss the Collins-Soper-Sterman (CSS) form of TMD factorization in the updated 
version presented in Ref.~\cite{Collins:2011zzd}.  (See Ref.~\cite{Rogers:2015sqa} for a general overview and for references.) For these proceedings, the relevant aspects of the TMD factorization theorems are the following:
